onId=775074&privcapId=113980611 |title=Are you a robot? |publisher=Bloomberg |date= |accessdate=2019-09-10}}</ref> Vista Equity has offices in [[Austin, Texas]]; [[Chicago|Chicago, Illinois]]; and [[San Francisco|San Francisco, California]].<ref name=crunchbase>{{cite web |title= Vista Equity Partners |url= http://www.crunchbase.com/financial-organization/vista-equity-partners |work= Crunchbase |accessdate= November 1, 2013 }}</ref> In 2018, Vista had over [[US$]]43 billion in cumulative capital commitments and owned over 50 software companies which combined, employed 65,000 people worldwide.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.pcmag.com/article/364594/vista-equity-the-biggest-software-group-youve-never-heard|title=Vista Equity: The Biggest Software Group You've Never Heard Of|work=PCMAG|access-date=2020-02-05}}</ref> In 2016, Vista operated with approximately $10 billion in their VI fund.<ref name=fundvi>{{cite web |title=Vista Equity Sets $10 Billion Upper Limit For New Fund |date= March 16, 2016 |author= Dawn Lim |url= https://www.wsj.com/articles/vista-equity-sets-10-billion-upper-limit-for-new-fund-1458129602 |work= Wall Street Journal |accessdate= October 16, 2016 }}</ref>\n\n\n==Investments==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Date\n! Acquisition\n|-\n| January 2001\n| Vista made an investment in [[BigMachines]],<ref name=\"cnet\">{{Cite news |url= http://news.cnet.com/BigMachines-reels-in-29-million/2110-1017_3-254310.html |title= BigMachines reels in $29 million |website=news.cnet.com|author= Melanie Austria Farmer |date= March 19, 2001 |accessdate= October 31, 2013 }}</ref> a provider of [[Configure, price and quote|product configuration]] software. Vista made additional investments in the company through 2012,<ref>{{Cite news |title= BigMachines Secures Additional Growth Investment |work= Press release |publisher=  BigMachines, Inc |url= http://www.bigmachines.com/bigmachines-secures-additional-growth-investment.php |date= September 17, 2013 |accessdate= October 